    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA292-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu iravukkuṟi maṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what refused a night tryst.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA292">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            neṭuṅta ṇārak kalaṅkuciṉai valanta</l>
<l>            pacuṅkē ḻilaiya naṟuṅkoṭit tamālan</l>
<l>            tīntēṉ koḷpavar vāṅkupu pariyum</l>
<l>            yāṇar vaippiṟ kāṉa meṉṉāy</l>
<l>            kaḷiṟuporak karainta kayavāyk kuṇṭukarai </l>
<l>            yoḷiṟuvāṉ paḷiṅkoṭu cempoṉ miṉṉuṅ</l>
<l>            karuṅkaṟ kāṉyāṟ ṟaruñcuḻi vaḻaṅkuṅ</l>
<l>            karāam pēṇā yiravuvariṉ</l>
<l>            vāḻē ṉaiya maikūr paṉiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>You who don’t think of the forest with fertile regions,</l>
<l>where the Tamālam in fragrant creepers with green lustrous leaves</l>
<l>that encircled the stirring branches of the long cool<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">neṭum taṇ āram</term>: this attribute of the sandal looks strange (unless we suppose that the first part of the attribute refers to the tree, the second to the paste), but the variant <term xml:lang="ta">neṭum kaṇ</term> is even less satisfactory.</note> sandal</l>
<l>is in distress when bent by those who take sweet honey,</l>
<l>you who don’t care for crocodiles,</l>
<l>that roam the difficult whirling of the forest river with black stones,</l>
<l>where red gold flashes together with bright white crystals</l>
<l>on the deep shore in the depth worn away when the elephant</l>
<l>dashes along,</l>
<l>if you come at night</l>
<l>I won’t live, sir, in the dark abundant dew.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
